definition.value: Nuclear particle of zero charge, spin 1/2 and rest mass of 1.008664904(14) u.
Atom-like pair of particles consisting of an anti-electron (positron) and an electron.
Elementary particle not affected by the strong force having a spin 1/2, a positive elementary charge and a rest mass of 0.000548579903(13) u, or 0.51099906(15) MeV.
A group used for compounds where a trivalent N atom replaces the group CH.
1-Benzofuran substituted at C-2 and C-3 by an ethyl group and a 3,5-dibromo-4-hydroxybenzoyl group respectively. An inhibitor of CYP2C9, it is used as an anti-gout medication.
An organic sulfamate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfamate OH group of benzenamine sulfate.
A monovalent inorganic anion obtained by deprotonation of hypofluorous acid.
An octadecadienoate with cis- double bonds at the 9- and 12- positions; the conjugate base of linoleic acid.
A tetrasaccharide comprising residues of galactose, N-acetylglucosamine, galactose and glucose in a linear sequence, all joined by beta-linkages.
A diamino-1,3,5-triazine that is N-tert-butyl-N'-methyl-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine substituted by a chloro group at position 6.
A methoxy-1,3,5-triazine that is  6-methoxy-1,3,5-triazine-2,4-diamine in which one of the hydrogens of each amino group has been replaced by an ethyl group.
